6.71	Gurkha_Contingent	Gurkha Contingent	The Gurkha Contingent (Abbreviation: GC; Chinese: ; pinyin: gūjiā jǐngchátuán; Chinese: , Nepali: ) is a line department of the Singapore Police Force. Members of the GC are trained to be highly-skilled and are selected for their display of strong discipline and dedication in their tasks. The principal role of the contingent is to be a special guard force, and it is currently used as a counter-terrorist force.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Gurkha_IOC_1.jpg/220px-Gurkha_IOC_1.jpg
